The University of KwaZulu-Natal has announced the appointment of Chief Justice Mogoeng Mogoeng as its Chancellor.Chairperson of the Council, Rev Dr. Vukile Mehana welcomed the appointment saying &#8220;the University was indeed fortunate to have the eminent Chief Justice serve as Chancellor and we look forward to interacting with him in this critical role.&#8221;Mogoeng takes over the position from his predecessor ANC National Treasurer Dr. Zweli Mkhize.Mehana also thanked also thanked Mkhize for his &#8220;distinguished service to the University,&#8221;.Mogoeng holds a B Juris and Bachelor of Laws (LLB) degrees from the Universities of Zululand and Natal respectively.The Chief Justice joins a list of other prominent figures to recently be bestowed the honour.Former President Thabo Mbeki was earlier this year inaugurated University of South Africa (Unisa) chancellor during a ceremony where condemned attacks on African migrants in the country following recent xenophobic flare ups in some areas around Gauteng.In March Chairperson of the National Council of Provinces, Thandi Modise was appointed Chancellor of the Cape Peninsula University of Technology (CPUT) taking over from former Finance Minister Trevor Manuel.-Siphiwe Mchunu